[West Nile virus reports from the USA continue to be sporadic.
National reports have not yet appeared. So far surveillance in Canada
has resulted only in the detection of West Nile virus in a fraction
of dead birds examined in Ontario. The confirmed West Nile
virus-positive birds were found in all 12 counties in the province. -
Mod.CP]
[As many of the States in the USA are just beginning formal surveillance for
WNV, one would expect that reports of WNV positive birds and mosquito pools
will start increasing as official surveillance begins -- a result of 'seek
and ye shall find'. - Mod.MP]
